00052 void TCPSACKRexmitQueue::discardUpTo(uint32 seqNum)
00053 {
00054     if (rexmitQueue.empty())
00055         return;
00056 
00057     ASSERT(seqLE(begin,seqNum) && seqLE(seqNum,end));
00058     begin = seqNum;
00059 
00060     RexmitQueue::iterator i = rexmitQueue.begin();
00061     while (i!=rexmitQueue.end()) // discard/delete regions from rexmit queue, which have been acked
00062     {
00063         if (seqLess(i->beginSeqNum,begin))
00064             i = rexmitQueue.erase(i);
00065         else
00066             i++;
00067     }
00068 
00069     // update begin and end of rexmit queue
00070     if (rexmitQueue.empty())
00071         begin = end = 0;
00072     else
00073     {
00074         i = rexmitQueue.begin();
00075         begin = i->beginSeqNum;
00076         i = rexmitQueue.end();
00077         end = i->endSeqNum;
00078     }
00079 }

00081 void TCPSACKRexmitQueue::enqueueSentData(uint32 fromSeqNum, uint32 toSeqNum)
00082 {
00083     bool found = false;
00084 
00085     tcpEV << "rexmitQ: " << str() << " enqueueSentData [" << fromSeqNum << ".." << toSeqNum << ")\n";
00086 
00087     Region region;
00088     region.beginSeqNum = fromSeqNum;
00089     region.endSeqNum = toSeqNum;
00090     region.sacked = false;
00091     region.rexmitted = false;
00092 
00093     if (getQueueLength()==0)
00094     {
00095         begin = fromSeqNum;
00096         end = toSeqNum;
00097         rexmitQueue.push_back(region);
00098         tcpEV << "rexmitQ: rexmitQLength=" << getQueueLength() << "\n";
00099         return;
00100     }
00101 
00102     if (seqLE(begin,fromSeqNum) && seqLE(toSeqNum,end))
00103     {
00104         // Search for region in queue!
00105         RexmitQueue::iterator i = rexmitQueue.begin();
00106         while (i!=rexmitQueue.end())
00107         {
00108             if (i->beginSeqNum == fromSeqNum && i->endSeqNum == toSeqNum)
00109             {
00110                 i->rexmitted=true; // set rexmitted bit
00111                 found = true;
00112             }
00113             i++;
00114         }
00115     }
00116 
00117     if (!found)
00118     {
00119         end = toSeqNum;
00120         rexmitQueue.push_back(region);
00121     }
00122     tcpEV << "rexmitQ: rexmitQLength=" << getQueueLength() << "\n";
00123 }

00201 uint32 TCPSACKRexmitQueue::checkRexmitQueueForSackedOrRexmittedSegments(uint32 fromSeqNum)
00202 {
00203     uint32 counter = 0;
00204 
00205     if (fromSeqNum==0 || rexmitQueue.empty() || !(seqLE(begin,fromSeqNum) && seqLE(fromSeqNum,end)))
00206         return counter;
00207 
00208     RexmitQueue::iterator i = rexmitQueue.begin();
00209     while (i!=rexmitQueue.end())
00210     {
00211         // search for fromSeqNum (snd_nxt)
00212         if (i->beginSeqNum == fromSeqNum)
00213             break;
00214         else
00215             i++;
00216     }
00217 
00218     // search for adjacent sacked/rexmitted regions
00219     while (i!=rexmitQueue.end())
00220     {
00221         if (i->sacked || i->rexmitted)
00222         {
00223             counter = counter + (i->endSeqNum - i->beginSeqNum);
00224 
00225             // adjacent regions?
00226             uint32 tmp = i->endSeqNum;
00227             i++;
00228             if (i->beginSeqNum != tmp)
00229                 break;
00230         }
00231         else
00232             break;
00233     }
00234     return counter;
00235 }

00280     if (rexmitQueue.empty() || seqGE(seqNum,end))

00306 uint32 TCPSACKRexmitQueue::getNumOfDiscontiguousSacks(uint32 seqNum)
00307 {
00308     uint32 counter = 0;
00309 
00310     if (rexmitQueue.empty() || seqGE(seqNum,end))
00311         return counter;
00312 
00313     RexmitQueue::iterator i = rexmitQueue.begin();
00314     while (i!=rexmitQueue.end() && seqLess(i->beginSeqNum, seqNum)) // search for seqNum
00315     {
00316         i++;
00317         if (i->beginSeqNum == seqNum)
00318             break;
00319     }
00320 
00321     ASSERT(seqLE(seqNum,i->beginSeqNum) || seqGE(seqNum,--i->endSeqNum));
00322 
00323     // search for discontiguous sacked regions
00324     while (i!=rexmitQueue.end())
00325     {
00326         if (i->sacked)
00327         {
00328             counter++;
00329             uint32 tmp = i->endSeqNum;
00330             i++;
00331             while (i->sacked && i->beginSeqNum == tmp && i!=rexmitQueue.end()) // adjacent sacked regions?
00332             {
00333                 tmp = i->endSeqNum;
00334                 i++;
00335             }
00336         }
00337         else
00338             i++;
00339     }
